<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870227-0170 </DOCNO><HL> Standard Oil-BP Joint Venture</HL><DD> 02/27/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> SRD BPPETROLEUM (PET) </IN><DATELINE> CLEVELAND  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Standard Oil Co. and BP North America Inc., a subsidiary of the British Petroleum Co., said they will form a joint venture to manage financial trading activities for the two companies, beginning in April.    The venture will be able to manage the money market borrowing and investment activities of both companies and also will trade foreign exchange and fixed income securities for its own account. It will be named BP/Standard Financial Trading and will be located here.    Standard Oil is 55% owned by British Petroleum. </TEXT></DOC>